cedented." and a "shocking history lesson." Illustrated with family photographs, newspaper clippings, and facsimile pages, Lindgren's diaries provide an intensely personal and vivid account of Europe during the war.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 0aAuthors, Swedishy20th centuryvBiography. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zSweden. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh1 aDeath, Sarah08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2016z978311066771440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224481423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300224481.jpg  a978-3-11-066771-4  YUP eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO